TopicTitle: What could this be? (sorry for the thumbnails)

Articles.Content: So I was launching a deep space probe to orbit Minmus when I saw this[ATTACH=CONFIG]32736[/ATTACH][ATTACH=CONFIG]32737[/ATTACH] Does anybody know what that could be, I didn't see it long so it could be just a few mountains, but I'd have to check it out again.

If you're talking about the white-ish ripples, there's a bit of a glitch in the way light sources shine on the surfaces of worlds. Those hills are receiving direct sunlight, even though the planet should be in the way.
Ok, I passed over pretty quick so I got the shots and put them up here. Thanks for the replies everybody:)
